Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler or grill to medium-high. Bring a
large #pot{} of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Slice @zucchini{1} on a diagonal into
long, ½-inch-thick slices. Halve @grape tomatoes{4}(halved). Cut @fresh
mozzarella{4%oz} into ½-inch cubes. Drain half the @corn{1/2%can} from can (use the
rest as you like). Pick @dried basil{} and @oregano{1/4%tsp}(finely chopped) leaves
from stems, then finely chop until you have 1 TBSP.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, dried basil, oregano,
@red wine vinegar{1 1/2%tbsp}, and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then set aside.

> We sent more garlic powder and vinegar than needed.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain well and transfer to a large #bowl{}.

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Broil until lightly charred, about ~{12%minutes}, flipping
halfway through. Transfer to bowl with penne.

> TIP: If grilling, place oiled and seasoned zucchini slices directly onto grates
> and grill until tender, 5-6 minutes per side.

Prick @Italian chicken sausage{2}(pricked all over with fork) all over with a
#fork{}. Place on same baking sheet and broil until browned and cooked through,
~{5-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to
handle, slice diagonally into ½-inch-thick slices.

> TIP: If grilling, place sausages directly onto grates and grill until cooked
> through, 5-6 minutes per side.

Add tomatoes, mozzarella, corn, @arugula{2%cups}, sausage, and vinaigrette to bowl
with penne and zucchini. Toss to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and
serve.